---

<section id="faq" class="py-20 px-6 bg-gray-950 border-t border-gray-800">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400">Common questions from students and organizations</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Student FAQs -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600/30 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-400">For Students & Individuals</h3>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-blue-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">I'm a beginner. Can I still learn thick client or embedded security?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Absolutely! We start with fundamentals and build up gradually. While some basic IT knowledge helps, we've successfully trained complete beginners in these niche areas. The key is motivation and practice.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-blue-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Do you offer student discounts or payment plans?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Yes! We offer student-friendly pricing (RM 500-1,500 per course) and flexible payment plans. We believe financial barriers shouldn't prevent motivated learners from gaining valuable skills.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-blue-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Will this training help me get a cybersecurity job?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Absolutely! Learning niche skills like thick client security, embedded systems, or mobile app testing sets you apart from other candidates. Many employers specifically seek these rare skills. We also provide career guidance and portfolio project support.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-blue-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Can I learn on evenings or weekends?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Yes! We offer flexible scheduling including evening and weekend sessions to accommodate students and working professionals. Self-paced components let you learn at your own speed.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-blue-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Do I get a certificate upon completion?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Yes! All students who complete the training receive a certificate of completion. More importantly, you'll have hands-on project work to showcase in your portfolio and interviews.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Organization FAQs -->
    <div>
      <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-green-600/30 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-3">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">For Organizations & Teams</h3>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">How long does it take to train our team to find bugs before pentests?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Typically 2-4 weeks depending on your team's existing skills and the complexity of your applications. After training, teams usually catch 60-70% of vulnerabilities in-house within the first 3 months.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Can you train our team on our specific legacy thick client apps?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Absolutely! That's our specialty. We customize training to your exact tech stack—whether it's VB.NET, WinForms, WPF, Delphi, or other legacy systems. We work with your actual applications when possible for maximum relevance.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What's the ROI compared to traditional pentesting?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Training costs RM 5K-15K one-time vs. RM 50K-80K per pentest. Organizations typically save 60-80% annually by catching bugs in-house. Plus, you build permanent internal capability instead of dependency on external consultants.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Do you provide post-training support?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>Yes! Corporate training packages include follow-up support via email/chat for questions that arise as your team applies their new skills. We also offer optional ongoing consultation services.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Can training be delivered remotely or does it need to be on-site?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>We offer both! On-site training is great for hands-on work with your actual systems. Remote training works well for distributed teams or when travel isn't feasible. Both formats are highly interactive and effective.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50 overflow-hidden">
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">What if our pentester says thick client testing is "too hard"?</h4>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400">
              <p>That's exactly why we exist! Most pentesters focus only on web apps. We specialize in teaching thick client, embedded, and mobile security—areas where external expertise is rare and expensive. Train your team to handle what others won't.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
